{"lemma":"مَرازِبَةٍ","slug":"مَرازِبَةٍ","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n15370"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B2%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"marzban, margrave, march warden, satrap, a Sassanian governor of a frontier province","tags":["historical"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a dry measure for grain, a fourth of a مَكُّوك (makkūk), ca. 26.25 liters","tags":["historical","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a liquid measure for wine, a sixteenth of a مِشْقَاع (mišqāʕ), 1.875 liters","tags":["historical","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Middle Persian [script needed] (mlcpʾn' /⁠marz(o)bān⁠/, “margrave”), whence Persian مرزبان (marzbân).\n\nAlso found in Classical Syriac ܡܪܙܒܢܐ (marzəbānā, “a serving of grain”) and Middle Armenian մարզպան (marzpan, “a measure of grain or liquid”). This is probably a suffigation of the word treated at مِرْزَاب (mirzāb, “spout”), i.e. “a spout full of grain”."},"ipa":["/mar.zu.baːn/","/mar.za.baːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15370","headword_ar":"مَرْزُبَانٌ","root":"rzb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A satrap;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Persians:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a courageous cavalier who is set over a people, under a king:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) it is said, on the authority of As, that the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajam","text_ar":"عَجَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persians"},{"kind":"text","text":"] was called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marozubaAnN","text_ar":"مَرْزُبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazorubaAnN","text_ar":"مَزْرُبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IB, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mrzbAn","text_ar":"مرزبان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an arabicized word, (S, Mgh,) [originally Persian,] used anciently: (Shifá el-Ghaleel, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAzibapN","text_ar":"مَرَازِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A, Mgh, K.) Hence, [and from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAzibapN","text_ar":"مَرَازِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirozabapN","text_ar":"مِرْزَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEuw*u biA@ll~`hi mina AlmaraAzibapi wamaA biA^ayodiyhimo mina AlmaraAzibapi","text_ar":"اَعُوذُ بِا@للّٰهِ مِنَ المَرَازِبَةِ وَمَا بِاَيْدِيهِمْ مِنَ المَرَازِبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I seek protection by God from the satraps, and the iron batoons that are in their hands"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (S Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marozubaAnu Alr~aA^orapi","text_ar":"مَرْزُبَانُ الرَّاْرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, K,) [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The chief of the forest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the latter word meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ajamapi","text_ar":"الاَجَمَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, TA,) and also pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~aArapi","text_ar":"الزَّارَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh;) an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmarozubaAniY~u","text_ar":"المَرْزُبَانِىُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for which ElMufaddal said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmazobaraAniY~u","text_ar":"المَزْبَرَانِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as referring to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuborap","text_ar":"زُبْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the lion; but As disallowed this. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["A","Mgh","K","S","TA","IB"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}